<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1228,1662,1796]" box="[189,310,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1817,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Female inner spermathecae consist of two sac-like fingers on each side, with a round sclerotized reduced outer spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[418,489,1852,1879]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="7.[189,241,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1310,703,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[189,1398,703,1926]" captionText="Figs 1–8. Female internal genitalia. 1. Hexophthalma binfordae sp. nov. 2–4. H. goanikontesensis sp. nov. 5. H. leroyi sp. nov. 6–8. H. albospinosa (Purcell, 1908). Scale bar =1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1255330/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), to a certain extent similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lotz, 2018" authorityName="Lotz" authorityYear="2018" box="[845,1080,1852,1878]" class="Arachnida" family="Sicariidae" genus="Hexophthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goanikontesensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[845,1080,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. goanikontesensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1088,1180,1853,1879]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but with only two inner spermathecae sacs. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
